[{"id":"FT2978","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>What is the magnitude of the work done by gravity as the object slides down the incline?</p>","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The figure shows an incline plane that makes an angle theta with the horizontal. At the top of the incline is a small wall perpendicular to the incline. On the incline is a spring positioned parallel to the incline and connected to the wall at the top of the incline. The other end of the spring is attached to a block that is on the incline. There is a distance x labeled on the diagram that goes from a line labeled Unstretched Position of the Spring to another line where the block is attached to the spring.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/b28ee8cabc3cb10df6c0abf99828c4d9/original.png\" width=\"198\" height=\"197\"></p>\n\n<p>An object of mass <em>m</em> is attached to a spring on a frictionless inclined plane that makes an angle <em>θ</em> with the horizontal, as shown above. The object is released from rest with the spring in its unstretched position. As the object moves on the plane, its displacement from the unstretched position is <em>x</em>.</p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p><em>mgx sinθ</em></p>","<p><em>mgx cos θ</em></p>","<p><em>mgx sinθ   cosθ</em></p>","<span aria-label=\"mg x over sine theta\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mi>m</mi> <mi>g</mi> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3E1C@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<span aria-label=\"mg x over cosine theta\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mi>m</mi> <mi>g</mi> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>cos</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3E17@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>"],"answer":-1}]